---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Credential store" currentSlug="credentials">
  <h1>Credential store</h1>
  <p>
    <code>src-tauri/src/credentials.rs</code> encrypts provider tokens
    (Claude, Codex, ...) at rest with AES-256-GCM. The wrapping key never
    touches disk -- it lives in the OS secret store (macOS Keychain,
    Windows Credential Manager, Linux Secret Service) via the
    <code>keyring</code> crate, generated once on first use.
  </p>

  <h2>Tauri commands</h2>
  <p>
    <code>save_credential</code>, <code>has_credential</code>, and
    <code>delete_credential</code> are exposed to the frontend. There is
    deliberately no <code>get_credential</code>/load command exposed to
    the webview -- decrypted tokens never cross the IPC boundary to JS,
    only presence/absence does.
  </p>

  <h2>Spawning with a credential</h2>
  <p>
    <code>spawn_with_credential</code> is a stub: it decrypts a token and
    injects it as an env var into a bare child process. It exists to
    validate the credential-injection path ahead of the real process
    engine, not as the final spawn API.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
